abstract: Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
snippet: Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Perhaps no issue has divided the field of Democratic 2020 presidential hopefuls more than "Medicare for All."
headline_main: Where Democratic Presidential Candidates Stand on 'Medicare for All'
headline_print_headline: Where Democratic Presidential Candidates Stand on 'Medicare for All'

abstract: Mr. Yang may have difficulty reaching the 15 percent threshold required to earn delegates in many caucuses.
snippet: Mr. Yang may have difficulty reaching the 15 percent threshold required to earn delegates in many caucuses.
lead_paragraph: BOONE — A couple of hundred people packed a Mexican restaurant for Andrew Yang, who was running late.
headline_main: The Yang Gang hasn’t settled on a second choice.

abstract: Several candidates accused the Democratic National Committee of changing its qualification criteria to benefit Michael Bloomberg, who is not competing in the first four states.
snippet: Several candidates accused the Democratic National Committee of changing its qualification criteria to benefit Michael Bloomberg, who is not competing in the first four states.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The Democratic National Committee released its latest debate qualification criteria on Friday, and as is tradition, some candidates think they’re unfair.
headline_main: Democrats criticize D.N.C. change to debate rules.

abstract: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
snippet: Inside the very weird homestretch in Iowa, where candidates were thin on the ground, but reporters were not.
lead_paragraph: OTTUMWA, Iowa — As excellent as the Bernie Sanders event was — as excellent as it was to hear from the filmmaker Michael Moore and to eat Ben & Jerry’s ice cream scooped by the actual Ben and the actual Jerry, longtime Sanders supporters — it would have been even more excellent, was the general feeling, if Mr. Sanders himself had been able to come to Ottumwa.

abstract: The Biden campaign sent its top donors a private memo on Friday touting that January had been the campaign’s “strongest month of fund-raising since launch.”
snippet: The Biden campaign sent its top donors a private memo on Friday touting that January had been the campaign’s “strongest month of fund-raising since launch.”
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The Biden campaign sent its top donors a private memo on Friday touting that January had been the campaign’s “strongest month of fund-raising since launch.” There were no numbers revealed in the memo.

abstract: He was the first candidate to reveal his fund-raising haul for the month.
snippet: He was the first candidate to reveal his fund-raising haul for the month.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Andrew Yang, the former tech entrepreneur, raised more than $6.7 million in January, his campaign said on Saturday, becoming the first candidate to reveal his fund-raising haul for the month. Of that amount, he raised $1.2 million on Jan. 31.
